    "REASON: The proposed signage and trough light, by reason of their design, size and the materials used, would be unsympathetic to the existing frontage, and detrimental to the appearance and character of the existing building, the street scene, the setting of adjacent Grade II Listed Buildings, and the Barnsbury Conservation Area. The development is contrary to polices Env11 (Advertisements and Signs) and D4 (Designing in Context) of Islington Council's Unitary Development Plan (2002), Islington Council's Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002), Islington's Shopfront Design Guide, Policy CS9 (Protecting and Enhancing Islington's Built and Historic Environment) of Islington's Core Strategy (2011), and Planning Policy Statement 5: Planning for the Historic Environment."
